Manchester United’s transfer target, Erling Braut Haaland, has reportedly chosen Juventus. The Red Bull Salzburg forward has apparently agreed to join Juventus in January, according to Corriere dello Sport. Italian news outlet report that the 19-year-old has met with Juventus officials and has decided to move to the Serie A giants. Other clubs interested in the striker are Manchester United, Borussia Dortmund and RB Leipzig and had held talks with the youngster. However, the Italian champions have beaten their European rivals to sign the attacker. Haaland has scored 28 goals in 22 appearances this season and has a release clause of £26million (€30m). Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.